Infer from Databricks URL
Inside your Spark job you can try:
Java
String workspaceUrl = spark.conf().get("spark.databricks.workspaceUrl");
System.out.println("Workspace URL: " + workspaceUrl);
Then map:
Java
if (workspaceUrl.contains("dev")) {
    env = "dev";
} else if (workspaceUrl.contains("prod")) {
    env = "prod";
}
👉 Problem:
URL may not contain dev/prod
Naming can change
Breaks easily across regions / accounts


Use Workspace Name via Tags (Indirect)
If your infra team has tagged workspaces in Azure:
You cannot directly read Azure tags inside Spark easily
Requires extra API calls (complex + not worth it)